The paper deals with the application of modern machine learning techniques to the field of melanoma diagnostics using digital pathology. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image segmentation and classification. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also discusses the development of a novel multi-stride fully convolutional network (FCN) architecture, which involves the use of deep learning techniques for image analysis. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

In addition, the paper involves the curation of a new dataset of patient cases, which may be of interest to researchers in the sub-category of cs.MS (Medical Imaging). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the Breslow thickness measurement, which is a key prognostic factor in melanoma diagnosis. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
